      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1467">
               <p>William, elder son of <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1465.xml"/>Richard
                     Morgan Sr</persName>. of <placeName>Dublin</placeName>, was a founding member
                  of the &apos;Oxford Methodists&apos; with <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName> and <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers1223.xml"/>Robert Kirkham</persName>, and led the way
                  in their ministry to prisoners. William became both physically and mentally ill in
                     <date when="1731">1731</date>, his final year of studies, and returned to
                     <placeName>Dublin</placeName> in <date when="1732">1732</date>, where he died
                  on <date when="1732-08-26">August 26</date>. Some critics attributed his health
                  breakdown to his ascetic Methodist practices. See Atmore, <hi rend="italic"
                     >Memorial</hi>, 277–81 (who misidentifies as Richard); <hi rend="italic"
                     >DEB</hi>, 792; Tyerman, <hi rend="italic">Oxford Methodists</hi>, 4–15; and
                  Vickers, <hi rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>, 245.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
